fields.title: System Installation
fields.content:
## Django ## This is a system installation guide for windows OS.
- Server: Aapche 2.2 - Database: Postgres SQL 9.x Please follow GeoDjango on Windows to setup the system:
[GeoDjango Installation Guide][1]
**Note:** please choose apaceh while installing OSGeo4W.
If you want to start an Apache server with WSGI, please remember to collect static files into the local server location.
python manage.py collectstatic
## WSGI ## In order to use django with apche, a module to host a Python application should be installed under the Apache server. The following installation guide is for windows system. - Download a [mod_wsgi ][2] for the corresponded version of Apache and Python - Copy the mod_wsgi.so file into the Apache module folder. If you install Apache through OSGeo4W installer with default settings, the module folder should be *C:\OSGeo4W\apache\modules* - Configure Appache. Open httpd.conf under ~$(Apache_Home)\conf\httpd.conf. Add the mod_wsgi.so:
# Example:
# LoadModule foo_module modules/mod_foo.so
#
LoadModule wsgi_module modules/mod_wsgi.so

At the end of httpd.conf, include wsgi.conf. For example:
Include "C:/Teeth_Project/site_dev2/apache/wsgi.conf"
For more configuration of wsgi, please see the [document of Python WSGI adapter module.][3] [1]: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.5/ref/contrib/gis/install/ [2]: http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#mod_wsgi [3]: https://modwsgi.googlecode.com/files/mod_wsgi-pycon-sydney-2010.pdf
